How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

S. Fox
5.0 out of 5 stars EASY to install yourself!!
Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2021
Verified Purchase
Replaced all 3 of these when one failed. (photo after only the first was changed). Easy to install: FIRST CUT POWER SUPPLY TO OPENERS, then simply remove the two screws holding each cover to the wall using a small phillips screwdriver, then loosen the two screws on the chip board that hold down the two wires, remove wires from old opener using needle nose pliers, then reverse process to install new ones. Turn power back on and you are back in business! Great product...only 1 out of 3 of mine failed in 14 years and it was the first garage bay that is used the most. Arrived fast and packaged well. The new ones look way better too!
